<code>
final_answer("To make a module available within your library project but not to external users, you should use `mod args;` instead of `pub mod args;` or `pub(crate) mod args;`. 

In Rust, `mod` without a visibility modifier defaults to private. This means the module is visible to the parent module and any of its descendants, but not to other crates. 

Example:

src/lib.rs:
```rust
mod args; // Private to the library crate

