2. The second section of code deals with removing duplicates from the list. This is achieved through using Perl hash `%seen` to keep track of seen elements. The `grep` function is used to filter out elements from `@list` and only keep those that did not exist in `%seen` before. This is different to the Python example which uses nested loops to perform the checking, as Perl provides a convenient way to achieve this due to its efficient hash and array functionalities.

